ownedComment.body:
General: ------------ The configuration of routing the Modulation Flag (i.e. a pin indicating active chirp) to an SOC GPIO is done by using 4 stages as follows: Stage (1): Test/Debug Mux at IP level (inside RFE Analog, e.g. TE)
  • Selection of debug signal group for this IP using register DEBUG_MUX_REG
  • This may not be available in all IPs; only requiered if there are more than 8 debug pins from the IP towards the SPIM
Stage (2): Test/Debug Mux at SPIM_CTRL HW
  • Selection of debug signal IP module or group to be routed externally using register DEBUG_MUX
  • The output signals/bits from SPIM Debug Mux are called "debug_signals_rfe_mmw[7:0]"
Stage (3): RFE Access Mux for routing RFE debug signals to/from RFE (RFE_DEBUG_IN/RFE_DEBUG_out) or FlexIO signals to/from CPU control (gpio_ipp_do_flexio/gpio_ipp_ind_flexio)
  • Resides outside of RFE in main STRX HW
  • Is programmed by RFE SW suing RFE_ACCESS_CSR register DEBUG_RFE_IO_CTRL
  • HW signals routed from RFE towards outside are called "DEBUG_RFE[7:0]"
Stage (4): Mux for routing DEBUG_RFE signals towards chip level GPIO through SIUL in STRX
  • Is programmed by application; out of RFE SW scope
Handling of Mux1 & Mux2 stages for TE signal indicating active chirp: ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ Option (I): Routing of TE grouped signals (including TE signal "mcuint_chirpstart_out" via SPIM externally: (1) Configure TE Debug/Test Mux as follows (see TE register spec): (a) Set register DEBUG_MUX_REG subregister DEBUG_MUX_SEL to "b00_0001" ("1") for "Chirp Ctrl" (b) Signal "mcuint_chirpstart_out" from TE is available at the TE Mux bit 0. (2) Configure SPIM Debug/Test Mux as follows (see SPIM register spec): (a) Set register DEBUG_MUX subregister MODULE_GROUP_SEL to "00" for "IP Module based selection" (This requires proper programming of subregister MODULE_SEL) (b) Set Register DEBUG_MUX subregister MODULE_SEL to "1" (enabling "debug_te" on Mux output bits [7:0]) (c) Signal "mcuint_chirpstart_out" from TE is available at the SPIM Mux bit 0. Option (II): Routing of TE signal "mcuint_chirpstart_out" going into SPIM as signal "mcuint_chirp_start_out": (1) TE does not have to be configured, since signal "mcuint_chirp_start_out" is an input signal to SPIM directly (2) Configure SPIM Debug/Test Mux as follows (see SPIM register spec): (a) Set register DEBUG_MUX subregister MODULE_GROUP_SEL to "01" for "Group selection" (This requires proper programming of subregister GROUP_SEL) (b) Set Register DEBUG_MUX subregister GROUP_SEL to "8" (enabling mcuint_chirp_start_out) (c) Signal "mcuint_chirp_start_out" from SPIM is available at the SPIM Mux bit 3. Since option (II) requires only a single SPI transaction (whereas option (I) requieres two SPI transactions), option is preferred and implemented.
